net.corda.core.utilities

Class Try<A>

  • net.corda.core.utilities.Try<A>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Try.Failure, Try.Success

    public class Try<A>

    Representation of an operation that has either succeeded with a result (represented by class Try.Success) or failed with an exception (represented by class Try.Failure).

    See Also:
    class Try.Success, class Try.Failure

      • on

        @JvmStatic
 @NotNull
public static <T> Try<T> on(@NotNull
                                                 kotlin.jvm.functions.Function0<? extends T> body)

        Executes the given block of code and returns a class Try.Success capturing the result, or a class Try.Failure if a Throwable is thrown.

        It is recommended this be chained with throwError to ensure critial Errors are thrown and not captured.
